Class HugeHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.AbstractHugeHashMap<K,V>
        • ch.obermuhlner.jhuge.collection.HugeHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys
    V - the type of values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class HugeHashMap<K,V>
extends AbstractHugeHashMap<K,V>
    A Map that stores key/value pairs in a MemoryManager.

    The implementation mimics a HashMap.

    Access to single entries through the key is O(1): AbstractHugeHashMap.containsKey(Object)}, AbstractHugeHashMap.get(Object)}

    In order to store the elements in the MemoryManager they must be serialized and deserialized to read them. This is done by a Converter which can be specified in the HugeHashMap.Builder. The default Converter can handle instances of all serializable classes.
